body_html: yes, (a, b) in a return gets parsed as a tuple, just like Tuple[a, b]. Eventually we should also change user-defined script functions to also return single arguments, but I held off because this would interact poorly with onnx.

body: yes, `(a, b)` in a return gets parsed as a tuple, just like `Tuple[a, b]`. Eventually we should also change user-defined script functions to also return single arguments, but I held off because this would interact poorly with onnx.
